RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 51. Maiden Claiming Purse 10000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PREACH IT GIRL pressed the pace from a two path stance, locked into a stretch duel at upper stretch and wore down the leader for the score. EASTER VISION rushed form outset and led the field around the bend from a ground saving stance, but was unable to fend off the late charge of PREACH IT GIRL. LIL' BIT OF CHROME settled in behind the pacesetting duo, was forced to alter path at top of lane and finished evenly but was no match for top pair in the end. SWEET OLIVE gave chase from a three path pose, floated out at upper stretch and failed to menace.

ENTRY.NAME: Preach It Girl
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed two path, wore down leader

ENTRY.NAME: Sweet Olive
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased, three path, floated out upper stretch, no menace

ENTRY.NAME: Lil' Bit of Chrome
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled, altered path top of lane, no match top pair

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 11000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIG NORTHERN RIVER stalked the pace from a ground saving stance through the opening half, trekked the two path while under urging near the quarter pole, tucked to the rail at top of lane and rallied along rail for the victory. TEQUILA REVOLUTION hustled from outset to first command, led the field along the backstretch, had a slight advantage at upper stretch, but was unable to fend off the rally of eventual winner in final sixteenth. GOLDBRIDGE was unhurried through the first half, circled rivals around the closing turn, rated widest at upper stretch, and finished with a late rush to procure the show. BLAKE FROM TISH lacked a needed closing kick after stalking the pace from a three path stance, and rating close up at the top of the homestretch. SCHLEICHER came up empty in the crucial stages after flashing early foot and sharing command in opening stages.

ENTRY.NAME: Big Northern River
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked, roused quarter pole, rail rally

ENTRY.NAME: Schleicher
ENTRY.COMMENT: early foot, unable to sustain bid

ENTRY.NAME: Goldbridge
ENTRY.COMMENT: was unhurried around the first bend, circled rivals, late rush

ENTRY.NAME: Blake From Tish
ENTRY.COMMENT: second flight, three path, no late kick

ENTRY.NAME: Tequila Revolution
ENTRY.COMMENT: early pace, couldnt hold off rally foe

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 3 5F Dirt CR: 96. Claiming Purse 18000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 3 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000, if for $12,500, allowed 3 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOVER tucked to rail shortly after the start, circled pacesetting duo three wide at upper stretch, and finished under a stiff drive to prove best in duel. TIME MACHINE was denied in duel after pressing the pace from a two path stance. JUST CHILLIN lacked a needed response to urging in final furlong after rushing from outset and leading the field from a ground saving stance. CANDY'S LITTLE TIP failed to threaten from a back rated position. OKIE UNION trailed from outset and lost ground to front runners with a wide trip.

ENTRY.NAME: Okie Union
ENTRY.COMMENT: trailed, lost ground with wide trip

ENTRY.NAME: Mover
ENTRY.OWNER: Black Fence Racing Stables and Caldwell J R
ENTRY.COMMENT: tucked, circled three wide through turn, best in duel

ENTRY.NAME: Time Machine
ENTRY.OWNER: Bankroll Racing and Samuel E Shaw III

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 4 1M Dirt CR: 71. Maiden Special Weight Purse 21000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MANDOLIN WIND stalked the pacesetter as the lone rival in second flight, closed the gap on leader around the final bend, headed that rival at upper stretch and proved best in the stretch duel for the score. SOMERSETSLASTRIDE rushed from the break and established a comfortable lead along the backstretch, was headed at upper stretch and failed to match strides with that rival in closing strides. PRINCE OF EARL settled into mid pack through the opening half, swung three wide nearing the five sixteenths pole, rated close up as the outer most of three at upper stretch, and finished willingly for the show behind dueling duo. HOLCOMBE established an inside track shortly after the start and failed to menace. MY CALANTE lacked a serious bid after settling in behind pacesetters and giving chase from between rivals. OKLAHOMA MOON steadily lost ground to front runners and never threatened.

ENTRY.NAME: My Calante
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased between rivals, no late bid

ENTRY.NAME: Prince of Earl
ENTRY.COMMENT: three wide upper, willingly for show

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 5 6F Dirt CR: 83. Allowance Purse 23000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR OKLAHOMA STATE BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BRING IT ON BABY forced the pace issue from a three wide pose, gained command mid turn and drew off from rivals in homestretch for the score. SINNIN N GRINNIN hopped at the break, trekked three wide around the bend, responded to urging nd finished a clear second. PATSY R pressed the early pace from a two path stance, rated within striking distance at upper stretch but was no match for top pair in closing strides. SUPERBLEA stalked the pace from an inside stance along the backstretch, lot ground to front runners around the turn, and showed some late interest in final furlong. MO ARETHA lacked a needed rally after settling in between rivals and trekking widest of all at upper stretch. MISS RITA rushed away for first command, led the field into the turn then eclipsed in crucial portion of contest.

ENTRY.NAME: Superblea
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked inside, lost ground in turn, mild late interest

ENTRY.NAME: Mo Aretha
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled between, widest upper, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Bring It On Baby
ENTRY.OWNER: Williams Janelle L Wert-Gray Stacia and Gray Travis

ENTRY.NAME: Patsy R
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed two path, no match, held show

ENTRY.NAME: Sinnin N Grinnin
ENTRY.COMMENT: hopped break, three wide, clear second

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 6 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 56. Maiden Special Weight Purse 25200. FOR ACCREDITED OKLAHOMA-BREDS MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OKIE CODE broke alertly, gained first command, led the field into the homestretch, kicked clear near the eighth pole and held off the late rallying rival for the victory. EURA NORTHERN SKY saved ground in early going, was in pursuit of leader from a two path pose at upper stretch, and finished with a late rush to be gaining on leader at finish. SUPRISING CODE came up empty and failed to match late stride after pressing the early pace from a three path position and swinging three wide at upper stretch. CAT TALE BREEZE lacked a needed rally along the rail to end a ground saving journey. OKIE HEAT failed to threaten from a back rated stance. SCANDALOUS AFFAIR came away slowly, trailed the field from outset and was vanned off

ENTRY.NAME: Okie Code
ENTRY.COMMENT: alert, clear lead, held off rally rival

ENTRY.NAME: Suprising Code
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed three path, three wide upper, unable to match

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 7 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 52. Maiden Claiming Purse 10000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MACER THE RACER hustled from outset to set the pace in tandem as the outer rival of three abreast, trekked the two path around the bend and drew off in final furlong for a clear score. TUFF MANDATE settled into second flight, trekked three wide at upper stretch and showed late interest to gain mildly in the end. LITTLE MAD MAX hustled from outset and established an inside stance to set the pace in concert around the bend before backing out of the bid in final furlong. NORTHERN ORBIT gave chase to front runners from a ground saving pose, and finished willingly but was unable to close on leaders in homestretch. RIGGED RIGHT lacked a needed rally after settling into midpack and travelling four wide into the homestretch. SILENT SAILOR chased the frontrunners from a wide position, maintained that wide line around the turn and lost ground to front runners. RED ACE pressed the early pace from between rivals, rated two wide at upper stretch and tired in closing portion of contest. PROBATION ROYALTY got loose during loading process, trailed the field from outset, and proved no factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Tuff Mandate
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled, three wide upper, mild gain

ENTRY.NAME: Little Mad Max
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside, in concert, backed out of bid

ENTRY.NAME: Probation Royalty
ENTRY.OWNER: Boyce Brian W and Boyce LeeAnna D

ENTRY.NAME: Silent Sailor
ENTRY.OWNER: Walker Harlan Walker Lori L Walker Chad K and Hanes Haley Walker

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 8 1M Dirt CR: 83. Allowance Purse 30000. FOR ACCREDITED OKLAHOMA-BREDS THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Multiple Winners Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KWONTRO rushed from outset to lead the field, never relished command, and denied all challengers for a gate to wire score. BRIGGSEY broke alertly and established a ground saving stance, pressed the pace along the backstretch, rated close up and two wide at upper stretch, but proved to be no match for tough winner in final strides. GOSPEL BUZZ trailed the field early before swinging wide at top of lane and rallying mid track to earn the show. CHEROKEE LEGACY was unhurried in the early going, closed the gap on leaders around the closing bend, and finished evenly along the inside. FRIGERATOR settled into mid pack around the opening turn, trekked three wide near the half pole and advanced on leaders but lacked a rally in the homestretch. HEPUTTHEACEINRACE lacked a closing kick after looming on the heels of pacesetter through the opening half while trekking four wide. HUNTER QUICK stalked the early pacesetter from a three path pose, was shuffled back nearing the final turn, and faded fast in closing stages. WILBERT gave chase from a ground saving position then tired in latter half of contest.

ENTRY.NAME: Frigerator
ENTRY.COMMENT: three wide half pole, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Cherokee Legacy
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated back, closed gap five sixteenth, evenly

ENTRY.NAME: Gospel Buzz
ENTRY.COMMENT: late interest mid track for show

ENTRY.NAME: Kwontro
ENTRY.OWNER: Swan Patrick E and Lewis Robert E

ENTRY.NAME: Heputtheaceinrace
ENTRY.COMMENT: loomed four wide, no late kick

RACE.RACE_TEXT: WILL ROGERS DOWNS RACE 9 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 71. Maiden Special Weight Purse 25200. FOR ACCREDITED OKLAHOMA-BREDS MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISSIN HOLLYWOOD broke alertly, assumed command shortly after the start and kicked clear in homestretch for the victory. SEARCHIN SAFARI pressed the early pace from a two path pose, swung to three wide at upper stretch, and finished a clear second but was no match for winner in closing strides. DEN'S DYNASTY stalked the pacesetter from a ground saving stance, was within striking distance at upper stretch, but was unable to match strides with top pair in final furlong. AMMENTHEDESTROYER was hesitant at the start, trailed the field along the backstretch and passed tiring rivals in the late going. FORT NECESSITY lacked a needed rally after looming boldly on the heels of pacesetter from between rivals. MAJESTIC FLASH gave chase from a wide stance and tired in crucial portion of contest. KENNY T failed to threaten from a back rated position.

ENTRY.NAME: Searchin Safari
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed, three wide upper, winner to much
